Docs.summary: Provides APIs to load android.content.pm.SharedLibraryInfo#TYPE_SDK_PACKAGE SDKs into the SDK sandbox process, and then interact with them.

remarks.para: Provides APIs to load android.content.pm.SharedLibraryInfo#TYPE_SDK_PACKAGE SDKs into the SDK sandbox process, and then interact with them.
SDK sandbox is a java process running in a separate uid range. Each app may have its own SDK sandbox process.
The app first needs to declare SDKs it depends on in its manifest using the <uses-sdk-library> tag. Apps may only load SDKs they depend on into the SDK sandbox.
